etomica.modules.rosmosis

Class MeterFlux

  • java.lang.Object
    • etomica.modules.rosmosis.MeterFlux
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MoleculeAgentManager.MoleculeAgentSource, IDataSource, IEtomicaDataSource

    public class MeterFlux
extends java.lang.Object
implements IEtomicaDataSource, MoleculeAgentManager.MoleculeAgentSource
    Meter to measure flux across a boundary or boundaries. If an atom is on one side of the boundary at one time and on the other side of the boundary the next time, then the meter counts that as a crossing. Each boundary can have a coefficient, such that flow into one region through boundaries on either side can be considered "positive" flux. If an IntegratorMD is used, flux will be given in terms of crossings per area per time. Otherwise, flux will be given in terms of crossings per area per step.
